    "costs": null,
    "actions_taken": [
      "BSEE investigators arrived on 6 June 2017 to conduct investigation",
      "Onsite investigation conducted to identify probable and contributing causes"
    ],
    "summary": "On 3 June 2017 at 1935 hours, a Blake Floorhand working on the stabbing board of the Blake 651 rig suffered amputation of index and middle fingers on his left hand. While attempting to reposition a Self Retracting Lifeline (SRL) cable that had become positioned behind one of the monkey board fingers, the injured person lost his footing on the slippery stabbing board surface. In attempting to stop his forward momentum, he grabbed the Torque Tube for the Topdrive. At that moment, the Driller was lowering the Topdrive, which made contact with the injured person's left hand, severing both fingers.",
